'I cannot sing any more,'
`Folly it may seem,'
`I know what it was that you last saw,'
`We have not decided our course,'
'We have drunk the cup of parting,'
`Well, what was it? '
`And so should I,'
'Glad I am to hear again the wind in the trees! We are still little more than five leagues from the Gates, but we can go no further. Here let us hope that the virtue of the Elves will keep us tonight from the peril that comes behind.'
' said Haldir. '
